Sentencas: Triple-doped ceria Ce0.76La0.08Pr0.08Sm0.08O2-delta (LPS)-based nanocomposites [LPS-(Li-Na)(2)CO3], [(LPS-(Li-Na)(2)CO3) - NiO], and [(LPS-(Li-Na)(2)CO3) - La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3] were successfully prepared by the solid-state mixing method and investigated by powder x-ray diffraction (P-XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), and energy dispersive spectroscopy (EDS), mu-Raman spectroscopy, and impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: P-XRD confirmed the formation of nanocomposites with distinct phases and the existence of carbonate amorphous phase.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: SEM analysis of the prepared nanocomposites revealed that both crystalline and carbonate phases were observed and were found to be overlapped.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: The elemental analyses of entire samples were carried out by EDS.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: Raman spectroscopy confirmed the formation of composites and the existence of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy revealed the highest total ionic conductivities of the LPS-LN electrolyte (4.6 x 10(-1) S/cm at 600 C) and (LPS-LN) - NiO anode (2.28 x 10(-1) S/cm at 600 degrees C), as well as the lowest ASR value for the composite cathode (0.51 Omega.cm(2) at 600 degrees C).
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications

Sentencas: Enhanced electrical properties of the prepared nanocomposites confirmed their suitability for developing low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Investigation of Triple-doped Ceria-Based Composite Materials for LT-SOFC Applications
